I"<p>Say hello to <a href="https://civicfolio.govfresh.com">CivicFolio</a>, a portfolio website theme for civic technologists.</p>

<p>The genesis of this project came from a series of conversations <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/cnwagwu/">Chizobam Nwagwu</a> and I had about how folks who are at the beginning of their careers can build an online presence for themselves within the context of basic civic technology tools, projects and principles.</p>

<p>We discussed how a digital presence is important, especially one that conveyed the principles that civic-focused designers and developers should showcase when presenting themselves to potential employers.</p>

<p>My suggestion was that itâ€™s important to show your knowledge by adopting and doing. Over the course of the past few months, I started to build out a prototype that</p>

<p>Simplicity, accessibility and how to use tools that better help civic technologists learn how to strengthen their operational transparency muscles.</p>

<p>CivicFolio uses Public Sans and the U.S. Web Design System for the front-end and Jekyll and GitHub Pages for content management and hosting.</p>

